com.io7m.jtensors

Class VectorM3F

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.io7m.jtensors.VectorM3F
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Vector3FType, VectorReadable2FType, VectorReadable3FType, VectorWritable2FType, VectorWritable3FType

    public final class VectorM3F
extends Object
implements Vector3FType

    A three-dimensional mutable vector type with float elements.

    Values of this type cannot be accessed safely from multiple threads without explicit synchronization.

      • interpolateLinear

        public static <V extends VectorWritable3FType> V interpolateLinear(VectorM3F.ContextVM3F c,
                                                                   VectorReadable3FType v0,
                                                                   VectorReadable3FType v1,
                                                                   double alpha,
                                                                   V r)
        Linearly interpolate between v0 and v1 by the amount alpha, saving the result to r. The alpha parameter controls the degree of interpolation, such that:
        • interpolateLinear(v0, v1, 0.0, r) -> r = v0
        • interpolateLinear(v0, v1, 1.0, r) -> r = v1
        Type Parameters:
        V - The precise type of vector
        Parameters:
        c - Preallocated storage
        v0 - The left input vector.
        v1 - The right input vector.
        alpha - The interpolation value, between 0.0 and 1.0.
        r - The result vector.
        Returns:
        r
        Since:
        7.0.0
